      "content": "Absolutely, the \"tough on crime\" approach isn't a *debate*, it's an accepted, battle-tested philosophy for public safety. You can legitimately debate the *efficiency* of a specific policy, but the underlying principle of deterrence through severe punishment is the only objective starting point. Failing to seriously punish violent offenders ensures that criminals view the system as lenient, guaranteeing more crime. Therefore, toughness is the non-negotiable bedrock of a safe community.",
